cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper deals with depth completion using deep networks, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new representation for depth and a new loss function, which are related to machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the challenge of avoiding inter-object depth mixing, which is related to graphics (GR) and robotics (RO), making these sub-categories less likely but still possible.
